
[1]retroactive

   RETROAC'TIVE, a. [L. retro, backward, and active.]

   Operating by returned action; affecting what is past; retrospective.

   A retroactive law or statute, is one which operates to affect, make
   criminal or punishable, acts done prior to the passing of the law.
